frameDefinitions: A State_of_affairs (a state or event) either holds or occurs, and is presented as being causally independent of other (implicit) states or events that might otherwise have been expected to be causally related to the State_of_affairs.

The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
The words in this frame describe entities that occur in some temporally-ordered sequence.
An Entity undergoes some change (the Event) that is (or is construed as) punctual.
Two (or more) people (the Parties, also encodable as Party_1 and Party_2) negotiate an agreement.
frameExamples: That they got the same answers is just a <t>coincidence</t>.
Describe in detail the <t>sequence</t> of steps taken during an emergency.
This <t>happens</t> to me all the time.
So far , we have <t>agreed</t>to cede 100km of coastline to Kiribati . DNI
listRoleDefinitions: A <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> (that is, an event or state) that holds independently of (potentially) causally-related States of affairs.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> holds.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>State_of_affairs</fen> holds.
The action that the agent undertakes to achieve the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the agent attempts to achieve by performing the <fen>Means</fen> action.
An entity directed by the agent as part of the <fen>Means</fen> action in order to accomplish the <fen>Goal</fen>.
A participant function of an <fen>Instrument</fen> or <fen>Means</fen> in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails
The place where <fen>Means</fen> action succeeds or fails.
This entity occurs in some sequence with <fen>Entity_2</fen>.
This entity occurs in some sequence with respect to <fen>Entity_1</fen>.
<fen>Entities</fen> that occur in some temporal order.
This role identifies the entity, concrete or abstract.
This role identifies the time when the event occurs.
This role identifies where the event takes place.

The individual or individuals that form the more prominent (i.e.
agentive) party of the agreement, as compared with <fen>Party_2</fen>. That is,
<fen>Party_1</fen> is generally encoded as the External Argument of verbs, and
peripheral FEs that do not make reference to the event itself
generally make reference to <fen>Party_1</fen>. Thus <fen>Manner</fen> is construed to be that of <fen>Party_1</fen>, not necessarily that of <fen>Party_2</fen> or the group of <fen>Parties</fen> as a whole.

The semantically (and grammatically) less prominent participant (or
group of participants) in the agreement. It is generally encoded
within a prepositional phrase (e.g. headed by with).
An expression of the commitment made by the <fen>Parties</fen> .
<fen>Topic</fen> is a description of the domain covered.
The group of individuals portrayed as equally involved in making an agreement.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> where the Agreement occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the Agreement occurs.

American sailors</fex>.
